"If we fought before," he said, "not letting the French pass, as at Schon Grabern, what shall we not do now when he is at the front? We will all die for him gladly! Is it not so, gen- tlemen? Perhaps I am not saying it right, I have drunk a good dealbut that is how I feel, and so do you too! To the health of Alexander the First! Hurrah!" 
"Hurrah!" rang the enthusiastic voices of the officers.
